<HEADLINE> Findings From MD-80 Inspections  </HEADLINE>
   By The Associated Press
<TEXT>
<P>
	   A rundown of findings through Monday in inspections ordered by the FAA of
MD-80 series airplanes, with the number of each airline's planes ordered
inspected and any problems found. Not all airlines had finished inspections at
the time the list was compiled:
</P>
<P>
	   Airborne Express, 75 planes, two jackscrews found to lack lubricant, both
lubed.
</P>
<P>
	   AirTran, 44 planes, two with grit in jackscrew grease, one failed movement
check, all three jackscrews replaced.
</P>
<P>
	   Alaska Airlines, 34 planes, eight problems found, four jackscrews replaced,
the others under evaluation.
</P>
<P>
	   Allegiant Air, three planes, no problems found.
</P>
<P>
	   American Airlines, 284 planes, one jackscrew lacked lubricant, relubed.
</P>
<P>
	   Continental Airlines, 69 planes, one with grit in jackscrew grease,
jackscrew replaced.
</P>
<P>
	   Delta Air Lines, 136 planes, four problems found, one jackscrew replaced,
one relubed, two under evaluation.
</P>
<P>
	   Hawaiian Airlines, 15 planes, two with shavings in grease, both jackscrews
replaced.
</P>
<P>
	   Kitty Hawk, five planes, no problems found.
</P>
<P>
	   Legend Airlines, four planes, no report.
</P>
<P>
	   Midwest Express, 31 planes, no problems found.
</P>
<P>
	   Northwest Airlines, 172 planes, one with grit in grease, jackscrew replaced.
</P>
<P>
	   Spirit, 25 planes, no problems found.
</P>
<P>
	   TWA, 131 planes, one with metal shavings, jackscrew replaced.
</P>
<P>
	   US Airways, 62 planes, no problems found.
</P>
<P>
	   US Jet Express, eight planes, no problems found.
</P>
