<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 8; Nasdaq Loses 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up eight points in
today's early going. Advancing and declining issues are fairly evenly split on
the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off two points and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
Stock Index is down fractionally.
</P>
<P>
	   There's not much upside momentum as the trading day gets started.
</P>
<P>
	   And analysts are standing by to see if yesterday's Valentine's Day rally was
a one-day love affair.
</P>
<P>
	   Overseas stock market averages are mostly lower. Bond prices are also lower
following a report that showed stronger-than-expected production at the nation's
factories, mines and utilities.
</P>
</TEXT>
