<HEADLINE> No Oscar Nominations for Jim Carrey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Rubberfaced comedian Jim Carrey may be scrunching his
mug in disgust after Oscar again snubbed one of his Golden Globe-winning
performances.
</P>
<P>
	   Carrey claimed best actor in a musical or comedy this year at the Globe
ceremony for his uncanny impersonation of the late gonzo comic Andy Kaufman in
"Man on the Moon."
</P>
<P>
	   But his name was missing from the list of actors nominated today for an
Oscar -- again.
</P>
<P>
	   Carrey publicly joked about his desire for an Oscar after winning a best
dramatic actor Globe last year for "The Truman Show," in which he played a man
who unwittingly lives his entire life on television.
</P>
<P>
	   In his acceptance speech for "Truman," Carrey thanked the "Academy" for his
Globe award, which actually was selected by the Hollywood Foreign Press
Association.
</P>
<P>
	   After the press group rewarded him again this year for portraying Kaufman,
Carrey quipped: "I'm the Tom Hanks of the Golden Globes."
</P>
<P>
	   However, Hanks, a two-time Oscar winner and frequent nominee, also failed to
grab an Oscar nomination this year.
</P>
<P>
	   Hanks' current film, "The Green Mile," received several nominations today,
including best picture. "Man on the Moon" got none.
</P>
</TEXT>
