<HEADLINE> Box Office Performance for Oscars  </HEADLINE>
    By The Associated Press
<TEXT>
<P>
	   North American box office performance for Tuesday's top five Academy Award
nominees:
</P>
<P>
	   -- "American Beauty," Dreamworks, eight nominations, released in September,
$75 million.
</P>
<P>
	   -- "The Cider House Rules," Miramax, seven nominations, released in
December, $23 million.
</P>
<P>
	   -- "The Insider," Buena Vista, seven nominations, released in November, $26
million.
</P>
<P>
	   -- "The Sixth Sense," Buena Vista, six nominations, released in August, $280
million.
</P>
<P>
	   -- "The Talented Mr. Ripley," Paramount, five nominations, released in
December, $78 million.
</P>
</TEXT>
