<HEADLINE> McLean Likes Madonna's Rendition  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Don McLean is more than happy with Madonna's piece of
his American Pie.
</P>
<P>
	   Madonna released her version of the 1971 anthem on Feb. 1, adding an
electronic dance beat and distant background vocals from actor Rupert Everett.
</P>
<P>
	   She also chopped more than 3 1/2 minutes from the original 8 1/2-minute
homage to Buddy Holly, Ritchie Valens and the Big Bopper.
</P>
<P>
	   "I have heard her version and I think it is sensual and mystical. I also
feel that she's chosen autobiographical verses that reflect her career and
personal history," McLean said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
	   "I hope it will cause people to ask what's happening to music in America,"
he said. "I have received many gifts from God but this is the first time I have
ever received a gift from a goddess."
</P>
