<HEADLINE> European Stocks End Down  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LONDON (AP) -- European stocks ended lower Tuesday amid losses in the media
and telecommunications sectors due to profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of European companies fell 7.84 points, or 2.2
percent, to 371.30, while the Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index ended 11.39 points
lower at 430.21.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index slid 122.75 points to 5,043.33, while the
DJ Stoxx 50 Index lost 109.50 points to 4,673.96.
</P>
<P>
	   Within the DJ STOXX index, media shares fell 6.0 percent and while the
telecom industry dropped 4.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   French media group Canal Plus tumbled 40.90 euros to 267.10 euros on
profit-taking following its meteoric rise since the beginning of 2000. British
Sky Broadcasting ended 119.5 pence lower at 1,687.5 pence, while the smaller
French media company Lagardere lost 2.0 euros to end at 96.10 euros.
</P>
<P>
	   France Telecom lost 13.50 euros to close at 158.20 euros, Vodafone AirTouch
fell 19.75 pence to 310.5 pence and Deutsche Telekom dropped 3.30 euros to
finish at 84 euros.
</P>
<P>
	   In domestic markets, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index closed 3.3 percent lower to
7,396.13 and Amsterdam's AEX slipped 0.4 percent to 652.34
</P>
<P>
	   The Paris CAC 40 index ended down 2.8 percent to 6,092.63, hit by the
selling of Canal Plus shares.
</P>
<P>
	   London's FTSE 100 index finished 1.0 percent lower at 6,005.2.
</P>
</TEXT>
