<HEADLINE> Business news in brief from around New Jersey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   MURRAY HILL, N.J. (AP) - Lucent Technologies said Tuesday it has nearly
completed a $30-million expansion at its Breinigsville, Pa., facility. It makes
optoelectronic components for Lucent, a leading telecommunications equipment
maker.
<P>
	   Optoelectronic components send light signals that carry voice and data
traffic across fiber-optic networks. Increased production capacity is needed to
keep up with the demand for high-speed Internet access, the company said.
</P>
<P>
	   The expansion program also includes a $6 million renovation at another
facility in Reading, Pa., which also manufactures optoelectronic components, and
is expected to create 500 new jobs this year in various Lucent sites.
</P>
<P>
	   ----
</P>
<P>
	   PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) - RCN Corp., a fiber-optic network operator, said
Tuesday it will build a broadband network in Seattle, Wash., and 11 surrounding
communities.
</P>
<P>
	   The company said its Megaband Network will offer residents bundled
telecommunications services that run on a network that is many times faster than
a standard 56K modem. There are more than 425,000 homes in the Seattle area.
</P>
<P>
	   RCN is to build an integrated fiber-optics network, allowing residents to
buy local and long distance telephone, cable TV and Internet services from one
company.
</P>
<P>
	   Existing RCN networks are in Manhattan, Queens, Boston, Chicago, South San
Francisco and Washington, D.C. The company posted $335.8 million in 1999
revenues.
</P>
<P>
	   ----
</P>
<P>
	   WOODCLIFF LAKE, N.J. (AP) - Ingersoll-Rand Co. announced Tuesday it has
acquired Neal Manufacturing Co. Inc., a Carrollton, Ga.-based maker of road
paving machinery and related equipment.
</P>
<P>
	   Neal is to become part of Ingersoll-Rand's Infrastructure Development
Sector. Terms of the deal were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
	   Ingersoll-Rand is a major diversified equipment and components manufacturer.
It employs 46,000 people worldwide.
</P>
<P>
	   ----
</P>
<P>
	   ABERDEEN TOWNSHIP, N.J. (AP) - iVoice.com Inc., a manufacturer of voice and
computer telephony systems, has agreed to purchase Laguna Hills, Ca.-based
MaiSoft Inc. for an undisclosed amount.
</P>
<P>
	   MaiSoft is a developer and maker of telephony and voice-activated
applications. Its Unified Messaging System manages individual voice mail, e-mail
and fax messages through a personal computer using a standard software program.
</P>
<P>
	   The acquisition is expected to be completed by March 3.
</P>
<P>
	   ----
</P>
<P>
	   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) - United Kingdom-based Acordis has chosen Prudential
Retirement Services to administer the 401(k) retirement savings plan for its
U.S. employees.
</P>
<P>
	   Acordis is a multinational group of businesses that supplies man-made fibers
and specialty materials for industrial, textile, medical and hygiene
applications. The company employs 16,000 people, 1,500 of whom work in the
United States.
</P>
<P>
	   Prudential Retirement Services manages more than $61 billion in assets for
more than 1 million plan participants. It is part of Newark-based Prudential
Insurance Co. of America, the nation's largest life insurance company.
</P>
<P>
	   ---- 
</P>
</TEXT>
