<HEADLINE> Oscar Snubs Carrey Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Jim Carrey may be the Tom Hanks of the Golden Globes,
but he's not the Tom Hanks of the Oscars.
</P>
<P>
	   Carrey's portrayal of comic Andy Kaufman in "Man on the Moon" failed to gain
a nomination for a best actor Academy Award on Tuesday even though the role
earned him a Golden Globe for best actor from the Hollywood Foreign Press
Association in January.
</P>
<P>
	   Last year, Carrey won a Golden Globe last year for "The Truman Show" but not
an Oscar nomination.
</P>
<P>
	   "I'm the Tom Hanks of the Golden Globes," Carrey cracked last month when he
got his latest Golden Globe.
</P>
<P>
	   Hanks won back-to-back best-actor Oscars -- and Golden Globes -- for
"Philadelphia" and "Forrest Gump."
</P>
<P>
	   Carrey has never been nominated for an Oscar. Hanks has four nominations,
including honors for "Big" and "Saving Private Ryan."
</P>
</TEXT>
