<HEADLINE> Philip Morris Opens Russian Factory  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    ST. PETERSBURG, Russia (AP) -- The Philip Morris tobacco company on Tuesday
opened a $330 million cigarette factory outside St. Petersburg.
</P>
<P>
	   The plant, Philip Morris Izhora, is to produce 25 billion cigarettes a year.
It is the largest of the U.S. company's three Russian factories.
</P>
<P>
	   The opening of the plant brings production of all Philip Morris brands,
apart from Parliament and Virginia Slims, to Russia, said Pyotr Lidov, head of
the company's external relations department.
</P>
<P>
	   The new plant becomes the fifth tobacco plant in the Leningrad Region, the
area around St. Petersburg.
</P>
