<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-15 20:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Children's Jackets Recalled  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Nordstrom Inc. is recalling about 2,250 infant and toddler
jackets because buttons on their flap pockets could be removed and pose a
choking hazard.
</P>
<P>
	   The federal Consumer Product Safety Commission said Tuesday that Nordstrom,
a Seattle-based department store chain, was recalling the jackets as a
preventive measure. No injuries have been reported.
</P>
<P>
	   The recalled jackets were made in pink or blue cotton gingham fabric, with a
hood and flap pockets. They were sold in infant sizes six months through 24
months, and toddler sizes 2T through 4T.
</P>
<P>
	   The words ``nowhere but nordstrom'' appear on each jacket's hood label.
</P>
<P>
	   The jackets were sold at Nordstrom stores nationwide during January for
about $34 to $36 each.
</P>
<P>
	   Consumers should immediately stop using the jackets and return them to any
Nordstrom store for a refund. For more information, consumers can call Nordstrom
at 1-800-695-8000.
</P>
</TEXT>
