   By GLEN JOHNSON Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) -- George W. Bush and John McCain swapped charges of
negative campaigning Tuesday night in a close quarters debate, their final clash
before the South Carolina primary. ``You should be ashamed,'' the Arizona
senator lectured his rival. ``Don't compare me to Bill Clinton,'' Bush snapped
back.
</P>
<P>
	   McCain said he had ordered his staff days ago to stop running all negative
ads.
</P>
<P>
	   But Bush, seated scarcely three feet away, waved a printed flyer that he
said attacked him harshly and had turned up on a car windshield earlier in the
