<HEADLINE> Blair's Salary Goes Up This Year  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Prime Minister Tony Blair is getting a 2.9 percent salary
increase, bringing his yearly pay to $180,300.
</P>
<P>
	   The government said Tuesday that increase over Blair's current $175,628
income takes effect on April 1.
</P>
<P>
	   The independent review body that makes salary recommendations approved a pay
raise of $253,300, but Blair opted for the lower figure. The review panel came
into effect in 1997.
</P>
<P>
	   Lawmakers and government ministers will also get a 2.9 percent pay raise,
Blair's office said.
</P>
<P>
	   That takes ministers' pay to $154,600 and parliament to $77,200. from
$75,000. The raises are above Britain's rate of inflation
</P>
<P>
	   President Clinton, who earns $200,000 a year, signed legislation last fall
doubling the annual salary of future U.S. presidents to $400,000.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
