<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-15 23:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blues 4, Thrashers 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Michal Handzus scored two short-handed goals as the St.
Louis Blues extended Atlanta's winless streak to 11 games by beating the
Thrashers 4-1 on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
	   The first-ever game between the franchises was a contrast of teams heading
in opposite directions. Atlanta is 0-10-1 in its last 11, and 3-21-4 on the
road. The Blues are 9-2-0 in their last 11 and lead the Western Conference with
78 points.
</P>
<P>
	   Pavol Demitra added a goal and an assist for St. Louis. Lubos Bartecko had
the other Blues goal.
</P>
<P>
	   Jamie McLennan, making a rare start in place of All-Star Roman Turek, made
13 saves in goal. The Blues have allowed only 2.05 goals per game, the fewest in
the league. St. Louis is 30-3-6 when allowing two goals or less.
</P>
<P>
	   Ray Ferraro scored his 15th goal for the Thrashers, who have not won since
beating Philadelphia 1-0 on Jan. 14.
</P>
<P>
	   With the game tied 1-1, Handzus and Bartecko scored 35 seconds apart midway
through the second period to put the Blues ahead.
</P>
<P>
	   While teammate Tyson Nash was in the penalty box, Handzus poked the puck
away from Maxim Galanov at center ice, skated in and beat Scott Fankhouser with
a wrist shot for his 15th goal.
</P>
<P>
	   Just after Nash got out of the box, Bartecko carried the puck into the
Atlanta zone and scored on a slap shot from just inside the blue line at 12:16.
Fankhouser was replaced by Norm Maracle at the start of the third.
</P>
<P>
	   Handzus got an empty-net goal with 2:55 left, again while the Blues were
shorthanded.
</P>
<P>
	   St. Louis, 22-3-4 when it scores first, opened the scoring 13:29 in on
Demitra's 25th goal. Demitra came in on a 2-on-1, faked Fankhouser out of
position and put the puck into the open net.
</P>
<P>
	   Ferraro tied the game at 6:03 of the second, beating McLennan with a shot
from a bad angle.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-15-00 2313 </TRAILER>
