<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McCain Flier Derides Bush Plan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The flier that George W. Bush waved at Sen. John McCain
during the debate Tuesday says the Texas governor's plans will leave a $3
billion deficit in Social Security.
</P>
<P>
	   ``George Bush's plan will threaten Social Security for our seniors! John
McCain's plan protects Social Security for our people!'' the flier said.
</P>
<P>
	   Bush said the flier had turned up on a car windshield earlier in the day.
During the debate, McCain denied that the flier came from his campaign, but he
later reversed himself.
</P>
<P>
	   ``That could have been put out last week before we stopped all ads,'' the
senator said.
</P>
<P>
	   The flier compares McCain's ``responsible'' plan for Social Security with
Bush, who ``squanders the entire surplus on tax cuts targeted to the wealthiest
Americans.''
</P>
<P>
	   It also compares the two candidates regarding education and special
interests, accusing Bush of rejecting campaign finance reform and wanting to
turn education over to ``Washington educrats.'' The flier encourages people to
vote for McCain in the South Carolina primary Saturday to ``keep our Social
Security system sound and secure.''
</P>
</TEXT>
