<HEADLINE> Celtics 101, Jazz 99  </HEADLINE>
    By TIM KORTE AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Kenny Anderson scored 19 of his 33 points in the
fourth quarter as the Celtics beat the Utah Jazz 101-99 on Tuesday night,
Boston's first victory over Utah since Larry Bird's playing days.
</P>
<P>
	   Paul Pierce scored 20 and made two free throws with 1:03 remaining to give
the Celtics a 99-96 lead. Anderson hit four free throws in the final 16.4
seconds as Boston snapped a 14-game losing streak to the Jazz.
</P>
<P>
	   The Celtics last beat Utah in 1991-92, Bird's final season. The victory also
was Boston's first in Salt Lake City since January 1988.
</P>
<P>
	   Antoine Walker added 19 points for the Celtics.
</P>
<P>
	   Karl Malone, well-rested after playing only three minutes in Sunday's
All-Star game, led Utah with 32 points. Howard Eisley added 19, Jeff Hornacek
had 13 and John Stockton scored 12.
</P>
<P>
	   The Jazz forced a final chance when Bryon Russell, who hit a 3-pointer with
2.9 seconds left, intercepted Boston's inbounds pass and called timeout with two
seconds remaining.
</P>
<P>
	   Russell inbounded to Stockton, whose running scoop shot from 10 feet bounced
off the close side of the rim as the horn sounded.
</P>
</TEXT>
