<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-15 23:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cruise Ship Evacuated Off Mexico  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   COZUMEL, Mexico (AP) -- Some 750 passengers, mostly Canadians, were forced to
abandon the cruise ship Carousel after running over rocks, seriously damaging a
propeller and causing an oil leak, Mexican authorities said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
	   The damage was done early Sunday, shortly after the ship pulled away from
the port of Calica on this Caribbean island, 40 miles south of the popular
resort city Cancun, according to a report distributed by Mexican maritime
authorities.
</P>
<P>
	   About eight hours later, the crew noticed the damage and ended the cruise,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
	   Small boats were sent out to the ship, owned by the British company
Airtours, to ferry passengers and their luggage back to the island. They were
then taken to Cancun airport and flown to Miami.
</P>
<P>
	   A company spokesman said passengers would be offered a cruise on another
boat or their money back.
</P>
<P>
	   The damage to the bottom of the boat caused a 50-ton spill, and
contamination has been detected along surrounding beaches, port spokesman
Fernando Valencia said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
